    </m:msup>
  </m:mrow>
</m:math>
</para>
<para id="element-79">Where “c” is the speed of light in the vacuum. An amount of mass, “m” can be converted into energy “E” and vice – versa. In a process known as mass annihilation of a positron and electron, an amount of energy is released as,
</para>
